---
import MarketingLayout from '../components/MarketingLayout.astro';
---

<MarketingLayout
  title="Pricing — Mailify"
  description="Mailify is free, open-source, and self-hosted. The only thing you pay for is what you'd pay anyway: your SMTP provider and your server."
>
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="shell">
      <p class="eyebrow">Pricing</p>
      <h1>Free to use. Self-hosted on purpose.</h1>
      <p class="lede">
        Mailify is MIT-licensed and lives entirely in your infrastructure. There is no
        Mailify-Cloud tier, no usage cap, no per-seat fee. The only costs you pay are the
        ones you would pay anyway: an SMTP provider and a small server.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="tiers">
    <div class="shell">
      <article class="tier tier-primary">
        <header>
          <p class="kicker">Always</p>
          <h2>$0 for Mailify</h2>
        </header>
        <ul>
          <li>Unlimited sends</li>
          <li>Unlimited templates</li>
          <li>Unlimited tenants via per-job SMTP override</li>
          <li>Multi-arch Docker image</li>
          <li>Cross-platform binaries</li>
          <li>All future releases</li>
        </ul>
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="/docs/getting-started/installation">Install in 5 minutes</a>
      </article>

      <article class="tier">
        <header>
          <p class="kicker">What you actually pay for</p>
          <h2>Your stack</h2>
        </header>
        <ul>
          <li>Your SMTP provider (Resend, SES, Mailgun, …)</li>
          <li>A small server or container host</li>
          <li>Postgres for the durable queue</li>
          <li>Optionally: a custom domain + reverse proxy</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="note">
          Most teams run it for under $20/month all-in. A 0.25 vCPU container plus a
          managed Postgres is enough for thousands of sends per minute.
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="support">
    <div class="shell">
      <h2>Want to support the project?</h2>
      <p>
        Star the repo. File a great bug report. Open a PR. Tell a friend.
        Sponsorship channels are coming soon.
      </p>
      <div class="actions">
        <a class="btn btn-secondary" href="https://github.com/donilite/mailify" rel="noopener">
          ★ Star on GitHub
        </a>
        <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/docs/contributing/overview">How to contribute</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</MarketingLayout>

<style>
  .hero {
    padding: var(--space-16) 0 var(--space-8);
    text-align: center;
  }
  .shell {
    width: min(100% - 2rem, var(--container-main));
    margin: 0 auto;
  }
  .eyebrow {
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-4);
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: var(--fs-xs);
    color: var(--brand-primary);
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }
  h1 {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: clamp(var(--fs-2xl), 6vw, var(--fs-3xl));
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
  }
  .lede {
    max-width: 42rem;
    margin: var(--space-6) auto 0;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-size: var(--fs-md);
  }

  .tiers .shell {
    display: grid;
    gap: var(--space-6);
    padding: var(--space-12) 0;
  }
  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    .tiers .shell {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    }
  }

  .tier {
    background: var(--bg-raised);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    padding: var(--space-8);
    display: grid;
    gap: var(--space-6);
  }
  .tier-primary {
    border-color: var(--brand-primary);
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-md);
  }
  .tier .kicker {
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-1);
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: var(--fs-xs);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    color: var(--text-muted);
  }
  .tier h2 {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: var(--fs-xl);
  }
  .tier ul {
    margin: 0;
    padding-left: var(--space-6);
    color: var(--text);
    line-height: 1.85;
  }
  .tier .note {
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-size: var(--fs-sm);
  }

  .support {
    padding: var(--space-12) 0 var(--space-24);
    text-align: center;
  }
  .support h2 {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: var(--fs-xl);
  }
  .support p {
    margin: var(--space-4) auto 0;
    max-width: 36rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
  }
  .actions {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    justify-content: center;
    gap: var(--space-3);
    margin-top: var(--space-6);
  }
</style>
